The Lagos Chamber of Commerce and Industry (LCCI) has said that the Federal Government should engage the private sector in order to tackle the nation’s ailing economy. Director-General of the chamber, Muda Yusuf, told New Telegraph in Lagos that government should have discussions with those in the private sector to enable it roll out the kind of policies that would grow the economy. Yusuf explained that if all the policy measures that were in place in the last four years would be the kind the private sector would be expecting in the next dispensation, there would be problem in growing the economy. In the light of this, the director-general stressed the need by the government to have engagement at a fairly global or microeconomic level with investors to tackle some crosscutting issues affecting the economy. To make the economy grow, Yusuf said government should engage all sectors of the economy at all levels. He said: “This is why there are ministries such as the Federal Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development (FMARD), Federal Ministry of Solid Minerals and Federal Ministry of Industry Trade and Investment (FMITI), among others.